cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with integrating unstructured enterprise data containing tables, which involves database-related tasks such as table detection/extraction and mapping table layouts to an appropriate schema. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of semantic technologies (RDF/SPARQL) and machine learning techniques to transform tables with non-relational layouts, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of query answering services, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses structured queries that require joining multiple interrelated tables, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
